**Most critical gap**: `dispatch/util.rs` has zero tests for all four functions. The most dangerous is `windows_version_label` — it has 11 conditional branches implementing Havoc protocol compatibility, including a build-number range check for Windows 11 (22000–22621) and a service pack suffix. Any misclassification silently shows the wrong OS in the operator console, and there is no test to catch a regression.

**Overall quality**: High for the files that have tests — `rbac.rs`, `listeners.rs`, `events.rs`, and `logging.rs` show thoughtful, scenario-driven coverage. The main weakness this run is `dispatch/util.rs` (completely untested) and `rate_limiter.rs` (tested for happy path only, missing boundary and edge conditions).
